author: app.com
title: Monmouth’s Seaborn practices after a year of waiting
text:
MORE WEST LONG BRANCH – Micah Seaborn emerged from the locker room Monday afternoon, dressed in practice gear and went through a two-hour workout as Monmouth University opened practice in anticipation of its Nov. 13 season-opener at UCLA.
That is something that the 6-foot-5 Arlington, Texas native never got to experience last season.
Seaborn was ruled ineligible last season due to academic trouble stemming from his time at now-defunct Dallas charter school Prime Prep, but that is now in the past. Seaborn got his academics together and is now eligible for a Hawks team many feel can contend for a MAAC championship.
